  "texts": [
    "To characterize the strain sensing unit in terms of mechanical and electrical properties, a linear motor was employed to exert a cyclic force on the sensing unit as shown in Fig. 2D.",
    "Figure 2E and F provides our strain sensing unit sensitivity measurement in a strain range from 0% to 100% by buckling and stretching, respectively.",
    "The sensitivity was derived from S = ΔV/Δε where ΔV is the relative potential change and ε is the strain.",
    "As for the buckling strain, linearity of the electrical responses and a sensitivity of 5 mV was obtained in a strain range up to 50% despite non-linear region occurred beyond the strain due to anomalous shape change.",
    "The signals in the non-linear region were differentiated with the difference in the width of time as shown in Supplementary Fig. 6."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}